original: Bodegård, Josef Helmer Valdemar, kyrkoherde, Édsbruk, f. 25/1/08 i Bå-raryd, Jönköp. 1. G. 36 m. Anna-Lisa Lundgren. Barn: Monica f. 37, Lars 40, Magnus 46. — Stud:ex. i Lund 26, fil. ’kand. 28, teoi. kand., prakt. teol. prov samt prästv. f. Linköp. stift 32. Past:adj. i Drothem 32, v. pastor i Adelöv 33, komm:adj. i Västervik 34, kyrkoadj. i Finspång 36, kyrkoh. i Västra Ed sed. 46.
translated: Bodegård, Josef Helmer Valdemar, clergyman, Édsbruk, born on January 25th, 1908 in Bå-raryd, Jönköping County. Married for the first time in 1936 to Anna-Lisa Lundgren. Children: Monica born in 1937, Lars in 1940, Magnus in 1946. He graduated from Lund University with a bachelors in arts in 1926, completed a masters degree in 1928, passed practical theological exams and was ordained as a priest in Linköping Diocese in 1932. He served as a pastor in Drothem in 1932, assistant pastor in Adelöv in 1933, assistant commissioner in Västervik in 1934, church assistant in Finspång in 1936, and as a vicar in Västra Ed since 1946.
